The problem is that Time can't do that. The phoenix is subject to time only
in the sense that its 500-year cycle will come to an end eventually,
heralding another cycle with a new phoenix. But Time does not have the power
to truncate the phoenix's life-span. To talk of Time destroying the phoenix
in her youth is absurd. Even if you could be said to be talking of the
phoenix fable at all when you talk of her premature death (since the fable
does not provide for it), such a cataclysm could only be effected by some
other agency - not Time.

